- a k8s pod with more than one container

- containers in a pod share resources

- shared resources
  - network: containers in a pod share same network namespace even if the port isn't
    open to the cluster

  - Storage: containers can use volumes to share data in a pod

REASONS FOR HAVING MULTI CONTAINER POD ENVIRONMENT

- You have an application that is hard-coded to write log output to a file on disk


